1
00:00:01,266 --> 00:00:02,569
[RJ] Because you chose Enrile,

2
00:00:02,702 --> 00:00:03,903
I don't count anymore?

3
00:00:04,036 --> 00:00:05,605
You said
you don't want to be friends!

4
00:00:05,738 --> 00:00:06,972
Because I still love you!

5
00:00:07,107 --> 00:00:09,509
I broke your heart?
You're still breaking mine.

6
00:00:09,843 --> 00:00:10,910
That's why I hate you.

7
00:00:11,044 --> 00:00:13,179
It's nice to have someone
who takes what I say seriously

8
00:00:13,313 --> 00:00:14,480
and doesn't turn everything
into a joke.

9
00:00:14,747 --> 00:00:15,881
[Naih] You're annoying.

10
00:00:16,015 --> 00:00:18,251
You sided with Ysay
instead of me.

11
00:00:18,385 --> 00:00:19,919
I'm your girlfriend!

12
00:00:20,652 --> 00:00:23,690
When are you paying
your 75K debt?

13
00:00:24,089 --> 00:00:27,160
I can lend you the money
if you need it.

14
00:00:28,228 --> 00:00:30,629
Now, I have the money with me.

15
00:00:31,797 --> 00:00:32,298
Hey!

16
00:00:32,564 --> 00:00:34,768
Snatcher!
Come back here!

17
00:00:34,901 --> 00:00:37,469
I don't believe that bullying
should be tolerated.

18
00:00:37,603 --> 00:00:40,906
Expulsion is the only
proper course of action.

19
00:00:41,374 --> 00:00:42,207
[board member 1] I agree.

20
00:00:43,143 --> 00:00:44,143
[board member 2] So do I.

21
00:00:46,246 --> 00:00:48,081
[board member 1]
I think expulsion

22
00:00:48,213 --> 00:00:50,616
is the only proper
course of action.

23
00:00:50,984 --> 00:00:51,784
[board member 2] I agree.

24
00:00:52,185 --> 00:00:53,253
[board member 3] So do I.

25
00:00:54,219 --> 00:00:56,121
[Headmaster]
I think the board is ready

26
00:00:56,256 --> 00:00:57,656
to decide on this matter...

27
00:01:00,759 --> 00:01:02,328
[suspenseful music plays]

28
00:01:02,462 --> 00:01:03,862
[Max] Excuse me, Headmaster.

29
00:01:09,835 --> 00:01:11,304
May I speak?

30
00:01:13,873 --> 00:01:15,207
Go ahead, Ms. Del Valle.

31
00:01:18,778 --> 00:01:20,180
Max, what are you doing?

32
00:01:23,081 --> 00:01:23,816
[sighs deeply]

33
00:01:25,451 --> 00:01:29,055
If Elle was expelled
for what she did,

34
00:01:29,855 --> 00:01:33,793
and Deib would be expelled
for what he did,

35
00:01:35,295 --> 00:01:38,164
shouldn't I be expelled as well?

36
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:41,935
I reviewed
the student code of conduct.

37
00:01:42,067 --> 00:01:43,802
And I should be expelled too...

38
00:01:44,736 --> 00:01:46,539
because on my first day
in Benison,

39
00:01:46,673 --> 00:01:49,542
I committed
an act of violence against Deib.

40
00:01:49,843 --> 00:01:50,843
I punched him.

41
00:01:51,710 --> 00:01:54,647
[Max] He did nothing to me
to merit that behavior.

42
00:01:55,581 --> 00:01:57,516
So shouldn't I be expelled too?

43
00:01:58,016 --> 00:01:58,852
Max.

44
00:01:59,185 --> 00:02:01,287
I didn't like what Elle did.

45
00:02:02,021 --> 00:02:04,656
She wanted to scare me because
she resented me back then.

46
00:02:05,658 --> 00:02:07,293
But Aimee and Choco
were the only ones involved

47
00:02:07,427 --> 00:02:08,661
in hitting me with a bat.

48
00:02:09,262 --> 00:02:11,865
My sister didn't know
until much later...

49
00:02:11,997 --> 00:02:13,765
that Aimee and Choco hurt me.

50
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,968
They hid it from her.

51
00:02:16,436 --> 00:02:18,805
She had no intention
of physically hurting me

52
00:02:19,771 --> 00:02:21,241
nor attacking me.

53
00:02:22,407 --> 00:02:24,711
That's why I don't think
Elle deserves the expulsion.

54
00:02:25,277 --> 00:02:26,812
[Max] What I'm saying is -

55
00:02:27,413 --> 00:02:30,349
yes, there should be
consequences for Deib.

56
00:02:30,483 --> 00:02:32,585
Even for Elle and me.

57
00:02:33,252 --> 00:02:35,687
[Max] There will be no true
forgiveness or correction...

58
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:38,056
if we just said sorry
and left it at that.

59
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:41,426
But let's not just look
at the bad things people do.

60
00:02:41,561 --> 00:02:44,463
How about the things
they did to change

61
00:02:44,796 --> 00:02:47,667
and stop making
the same mistake?

62
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:50,669
Ever since
our anti-bullying project,

63
00:02:50,802 --> 00:02:52,972
ever since
Deib's public apology,

64
00:02:53,105 --> 00:02:55,375
people here in Benison changed.

65
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:57,743
Bullying stopped.

66
00:02:57,877 --> 00:03:00,546
People have stopped
seeing bullying as cool.

67
00:03:01,213 --> 00:03:03,116
People
have stopped being afraid.

68
00:03:03,616 --> 00:03:05,151
The other day,
people weren't afraid

69
00:03:05,284 --> 00:03:08,187
to tell Deib
that they don't support him

70
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:09,955
because they were no longer
afraid of him.

71
00:03:10,088 --> 00:03:12,025
And he didn't get mad.

72
00:03:12,491 --> 00:03:15,562
He understood them
and respected their decision.

73
00:03:15,694 --> 00:03:18,764
If Deib continued bullying,

74
00:03:18,897 --> 00:03:21,334
I'll understand
why he needs to be expelled.

75
00:03:22,301 --> 00:03:23,635
But Deib changed...

76
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:26,104
and continues to change.

77
00:03:26,705 --> 00:03:29,209
I can say the same
for my sister Elle.

78
00:03:29,342 --> 00:03:32,512
I'd like to believe that I am
changing for the better, too.

79
00:03:33,145 --> 00:03:34,146
So please...

80
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:37,449
Please allow Deib and Elle
to stay here in school.

81
00:03:37,883 --> 00:03:40,687
Their transformation is evidence
of the power of kindness

82
00:03:40,819 --> 00:03:41,420
and friendship.

83
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:44,424
If we just open our hearts,

84
00:03:45,358 --> 00:03:47,526
we can learn from each other

85
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:50,462
and help each other
become better people.

86
00:03:51,598 --> 00:03:53,866
And isn't that
what school is all about?

87
00:03:55,501 --> 00:04:01,507
-[applause]
-[uplifting music plays]

88
00:04:11,484 --> 00:04:15,555
[applause continues]

89
00:04:22,127 --> 00:04:23,096
[mouthing] Thank you.

90
00:04:24,831 --> 00:04:26,665
["He's Into Her" by BGYO
playing]

91
00:05:21,286 --> 00:05:24,122
["He's Into Her" ends]

92
00:05:25,791 --> 00:05:27,726
Benison Bears Captain
Deib Enrile

93
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:30,495
and Benison legacy Elle Luna
faced the school board

94
00:05:30,629 --> 00:05:32,764
and the student body
in an intense trial

95
00:05:32,899 --> 00:05:34,634
that lead
to a harmonious resolution

96
00:05:34,766 --> 00:05:36,134
for everyone involved.

97
00:05:37,970 --> 00:05:39,137
Max, thank you.

98
00:05:39,271 --> 00:05:40,139
Max.

99
00:05:40,505 --> 00:05:42,175
I'm so proud of you.

100
00:05:42,307 --> 00:05:46,012
Elle, make the most out of this
second chance, okay?

101
00:05:46,411 --> 00:05:47,512
Yes, Dad, I will.

102
00:05:48,380 --> 00:05:51,918
I'm excited for you to be back
in Benison! Come here!

103
00:05:54,454 --> 00:05:55,487
Thank you, Maxpein.

104
00:05:56,488 --> 00:05:59,959
You finally had the courage to
speak up and defend your sister.

105
00:06:00,093 --> 00:06:01,160
-Mom.
-Macy.

106
00:06:02,161 --> 00:06:03,596
[Headmaster]
Congratulations, Ms. Del Valle.

107
00:06:03,963 --> 00:06:05,064
Good job.

108
00:06:05,197 --> 00:06:06,232
[Headmaster] Actually,
your defense of Deib and Elle

109
00:06:06,365 --> 00:06:07,699
reminds me
of when Maxim defended me

110
00:06:07,834 --> 00:06:10,370
many years ago
during my own student inquiry.

111
00:06:10,769 --> 00:06:12,872
You defended
the Headmaster before, Dad?

112
00:06:13,172 --> 00:06:13,872
Well,

113
00:06:14,774 --> 00:06:16,242
it was the right thing to do.

114
00:06:16,541 --> 00:06:18,745
And because
Macy asked you to do it.

115
00:06:19,946 --> 00:06:20,379
Stop.

116
00:06:21,113 --> 00:06:24,550
Excuse me,
I'll just talk to Deib.

117
00:06:31,456 --> 00:06:32,290
[Deib] Thanks so much, MOO.

118
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:34,427
[Deib] You were awesome!

119
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:37,262
You almost made me cry earlier.

120
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:40,899
Max, thank you.

121
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,968
[Evita] Thank you so much!

122
00:06:43,502 --> 00:06:48,274
You were so good. You're gonna
make an awesome lawyer one day.

123
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:49,375
[all laugh]

124
00:06:49,509 --> 00:06:51,711
Or a PR specialist.
Maybe a spin doctor.

125
00:06:51,843 --> 00:06:53,211
I'm Deib's father, by the way.

126
00:06:53,678 --> 00:06:54,279
[Daniel] Hi.

127
00:06:54,413 --> 00:06:55,882
Hello, Uncle. I'm Max.

128
00:06:56,014 --> 00:06:58,283
[Daniel] You made my son
look really good today.

129
00:06:58,850 --> 00:07:00,319
Like he did nothing wrong.

130
00:07:00,452 --> 00:07:02,622
I don't know how you did it,
but it was almost like

131
00:07:02,754 --> 00:07:05,858
you were lying but not lying.

132
00:07:08,093 --> 00:07:10,196
I wasn't lying.

133
00:07:10,329 --> 00:07:13,665
It is true that Deib is kind.

134
00:07:14,199 --> 00:07:16,536
And he deserves a chance
at redemption.

135
00:07:16,668 --> 00:07:18,571
Well, I hope
he doesn't disappoint you.

136
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:21,673
[Daniel clears throat]

137
00:07:23,041 --> 00:07:24,744
["Best Time" by BGYO
playing over speaker]

138
00:07:25,110 --> 00:07:26,178
[Lee] Alright,

139
00:07:26,312 --> 00:07:29,247
congrats Max and Migz
for defending Deib successfully!

140
00:07:29,382 --> 00:07:31,516
[applause, cheers]

141
00:07:32,084 --> 00:07:34,286
Guys, thank you very much
for the support!

142
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:38,557
Congratulations to Elle
for coming back to Benison!

143
00:07:38,690 --> 00:07:40,992
[applause, cheers]

144
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,528
Thank you, guys,
for welcoming me back.

145
00:07:43,663 --> 00:07:44,797
How does it feel to be back?

146
00:07:45,697 --> 00:07:46,833
I'm relieved.

147
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:49,802
The past couple of weeks
have been really tough...

148
00:07:49,935 --> 00:07:51,103
After everything
I've been through,

149
00:07:51,237 --> 00:07:53,406
I feel like I've been reborn
into a different person.

150
00:07:53,538 --> 00:07:55,307
[laughter]

151
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:58,043
You do seem like a different
person, Madame Elle.

152
00:07:58,511 --> 00:08:01,047
Your smile gives you a facelift!

153
00:08:01,180 --> 00:08:02,081
[laughter]

154
00:08:02,214 --> 00:08:04,684
Speaking of
aura-changing smiles...

155
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:06,786
We're super happy to see you
smiling again, Michiko!

156
00:08:06,918 --> 00:08:09,288
[applause, cheers]

157
00:08:09,422 --> 00:08:11,757
I've passed all my tests, guys!

158
00:08:11,891 --> 00:08:13,692
Congrats to all of us,

159
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:16,728
we overcame all the tests
and trials thrown at us!

160
00:08:16,862 --> 00:08:20,065
Because
we are here for each other!

161
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:22,134
Go friends, fight and win!

162
00:08:22,267 --> 00:08:24,069
[all] Hoo-hah, hoo-hah!

163
00:08:24,803 --> 00:08:26,105
[Michiko] Wait, Max.

164
00:08:26,238 --> 00:08:27,305
Where's Deib?

165
00:08:27,439 --> 00:08:30,942
In a family meeting.
He'll be here in a while.

166
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:36,182
The next time Dale's GCS score
improves, I think...

167
00:08:36,548 --> 00:08:37,917
we can bring him home.

168
00:08:38,683 --> 00:08:40,352
Alright, I'll go ahead.

169
00:08:40,952 --> 00:08:42,554
Nice to see you back,
Doc Daniel.

170
00:08:42,687 --> 00:08:43,990
It's good to be back, Doc Cris.

171
00:08:44,123 --> 00:08:46,359
Thanks for taking good care
of my boy.

172
00:08:46,491 --> 00:08:47,426
No problem.

173
00:08:52,565 --> 00:08:53,365
[Daniel exhales deeply]

174
00:08:54,066 --> 00:08:57,503
When Dale wakes up, he'd be able
to tell us who did this to him.

175
00:08:57,636 --> 00:09:00,105
[Daniel] There's a killer out
there who should be in prison.

176
00:09:01,039 --> 00:09:05,278
Well, actually, Deib found
a private investigator

177
00:09:05,410 --> 00:09:06,946
who has a lead.

178
00:09:08,047 --> 00:09:12,751
Agila was supposed to send me
a CCTV video, but...

179
00:09:13,152 --> 00:09:14,653
he hasn't sent an update since--

180
00:09:14,787 --> 00:09:16,989
This Agila,

181
00:09:17,490 --> 00:09:18,990
is he a licensed professional?

182
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:22,662
[Daniel] Come on, Deib!

183
00:09:23,328 --> 00:09:26,499
Are you stupid? You didn't
check his credentials?

184
00:09:26,631 --> 00:09:27,399
No...

185
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:29,769
I was...

186
00:09:33,172 --> 00:09:37,143
Hon, Deib was just
trying to help, okay?

187
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:39,946
This private investigator
of yours,

188
00:09:40,379 --> 00:09:44,015
is he the reason why you've been
withdrawing so much money?

189
00:09:44,683 --> 00:09:47,219
[Daniel] The bank's been
flooding me with notifications!

190
00:09:48,620 --> 00:09:49,455
Yes.

191
00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:55,427
You paid that guy so much money!
You've been scammed, you fool!

192
00:09:56,461 --> 00:09:58,496
[Daniel] When was the last time
you heard from this person?

193
00:09:59,065 --> 00:10:00,466
The night of the championship--

194
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:02,835
The night of the championship...

195
00:10:02,969 --> 00:10:04,570
That was several weeks ago!

196
00:10:05,037 --> 00:10:06,538
[Daniel] And you just said

197
00:10:06,672 --> 00:10:09,508
he hasn't sent you
any recent update

198
00:10:10,176 --> 00:10:11,309
from him.

199
00:10:11,844 --> 00:10:12,745
And yet...

200
00:10:13,111 --> 00:10:18,049
you paid that conman
75K just this week?!

201
00:10:18,417 --> 00:10:19,317
No, Dad.

202
00:10:20,152 --> 00:10:21,486
That was for Uncle Boyet.

203
00:10:22,687 --> 00:10:24,190
Because...

204
00:10:24,724 --> 00:10:27,559
They needed some help because
their house in Mindoro...

205
00:10:27,692 --> 00:10:28,494
got flooded.

206
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:30,162
So I needed to, you know...

207
00:10:31,529 --> 00:10:32,965
Wait.

208
00:10:35,201 --> 00:10:36,501
Who's Boyet?

209
00:10:37,769 --> 00:10:39,004
Max's uncle.

210
00:10:39,605 --> 00:10:41,573
Max's uncle?

211
00:10:42,073 --> 00:10:43,408
[Daniel] And he came to you?

212
00:10:43,542 --> 00:10:45,344
Max's father, Maxim Luna,

213
00:10:45,477 --> 00:10:47,779
is one of the richest men
in the country!

214
00:10:47,913 --> 00:10:49,447
Why didn't Boyet
ask him for help?!

215
00:10:49,581 --> 00:10:52,618
I volunteered to lend him money.

216
00:10:52,918 --> 00:10:55,321
I just wanted to help.

217
00:10:56,187 --> 00:10:57,556
[Daniel]
You volunteered to help?!

218
00:10:57,889 --> 00:10:59,057
Well, Deib!

219
00:10:59,392 --> 00:11:01,027
You're so naive!

220
00:11:01,159 --> 00:11:05,030
First this fake PI
that has scammed you,

221
00:11:05,163 --> 00:11:10,135
now this Uncle Boyet will surely
take off with your money, too!

222
00:11:10,269 --> 00:11:12,638
Dad,
Uncle Boyet isn't like that!

223
00:11:12,772 --> 00:11:13,806
He wouldn't do that.

224
00:11:13,938 --> 00:11:15,541
How can you be so sure?!

225
00:11:15,673 --> 00:11:17,043
Because I trust Max!

226
00:11:17,909 --> 00:11:19,177
And Max wouldn't be
the person she is today

227
00:11:19,311 --> 00:11:22,414
if not for Uncle Boyet
who raised her!

228
00:11:23,716 --> 00:11:25,017
[Deib] He's not like that, Dad.

229
00:11:25,784 --> 00:11:26,985
Not at all.

230
00:11:27,886 --> 00:11:28,653
Deib--

231
00:11:28,788 --> 00:11:29,587
[door opens]

232
00:11:32,424 --> 00:11:32,991
[door closes]

233
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:40,566
-[suspenseful music begins]
-I don't know what to do, bro.

234
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,067
I have a debt with Boss,

235
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:44,336
now I owe the person
I took a loan from

236
00:11:44,470 --> 00:11:46,038
to pay my debt with Boss.

237
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:47,972
Only one solution to that -

238
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,375
carnap again.

239
00:11:51,376 --> 00:11:54,080
But this time,
go through with it.

240
00:11:58,517 --> 00:11:59,350
Bro.

241
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,721
No! I can't do it anymore.

242
00:12:03,221 --> 00:12:06,991
Bro,
remember the man spying on us?

243
00:12:07,359 --> 00:12:10,428
Turns out he's not a cop
but a private investigator.

244
00:12:11,096 --> 00:12:13,599
Likely hired
by the victim's family.

245
00:12:15,668 --> 00:12:21,173
My God! What if
he's just around, spying on us?

246
00:12:22,341 --> 00:12:26,044
Don't panic. We're fine.
Boss's men just texted.

247
00:12:26,177 --> 00:12:29,048
They took care of it.

248
00:12:31,484 --> 00:12:33,619
What do you mean?

249
00:12:38,023 --> 00:12:38,557
[line ringing]

250
00:12:40,493 --> 00:12:42,894
[phone ringing]

251
00:12:44,129 --> 00:12:47,966
He's gone. Dead.
Boss took him out.

252
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:51,102
I'm at The Barb, Max.

253
00:12:51,236 --> 00:12:53,339
Hi, MOO. Just checking on you.

254
00:12:53,739 --> 00:12:54,440
[Tiago] You better pray...

255
00:12:55,006 --> 00:12:59,110
the PI didn't get anything on us
and gave it to the family.

256
00:12:59,644 --> 00:13:04,482
Because if he did, Boss
will come after the family next.

257
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:07,952
[Deib] Mom got something
for you. Wait I'll get--

258
00:13:08,086 --> 00:13:09,421
What the hell!

259
00:13:11,356 --> 00:13:13,926
-[grunting]
-What?!

260
00:13:14,493 --> 00:13:19,097
-[grunting on phone]
-Deib, hello? Hello?

261
00:13:23,936 --> 00:13:25,203
[grunting]

262
00:13:25,336 --> 00:13:27,472
Boss has eyes
and ears everywhere.

263
00:13:27,605 --> 00:13:29,807
-[grunting]
-[man] Beat him up!

264
00:13:29,942 --> 00:13:31,476
-[grunting]
-[man] Hold him!

265
00:13:31,610 --> 00:13:34,746
[Tiago] Everyone
who gets in his way dies.

266
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:39,118
-[grunting]
-[man] What?!

267
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:40,586
Mess up a job,

268
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:42,288
and you pay with your life.

269
00:13:42,421 --> 00:13:44,355
-[Deib grunting on phone]
-Deib, what's going on?!

270
00:13:44,856 --> 00:13:45,957
Max! What's wrong?

271
00:13:46,424 --> 00:13:47,960
Deib's being beaten up!

272
00:13:48,092 --> 00:13:48,826
-[friends exclaim]
-[Max] Deib!

273
00:13:48,961 --> 00:13:49,928
Come on!

274
00:13:50,062 --> 00:13:52,063
Guys, wait!
We'll go. Wait here!

275
00:13:52,998 --> 00:13:53,865
Be careful!

276
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:56,601
Speak up,
and you will be silenced.

277
00:13:57,235 --> 00:13:57,769
-[Deib grunting]
-[man] What?!

278
00:13:57,903 --> 00:13:58,403
[Max] Hey!

279
00:13:59,804 --> 00:14:01,907
Hey! Stop, damn it!

280
00:14:02,207 --> 00:14:03,676
[Max] What are you doing?!

281
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:05,577
What?!

282
00:14:05,711 --> 00:14:06,711
[grunting]

283
00:14:07,446 --> 00:14:08,047
[grunting]

284
00:14:09,248 --> 00:14:10,649
-[man] Shoot. My keys!
-[Deib] Max!

285
00:14:10,783 --> 00:14:11,450
[Deib] Go after them!

286
00:14:11,583 --> 00:14:11,850
[Lee] Max! Deib!

287
00:14:11,984 --> 00:14:12,585
Go!

288
00:14:13,985 --> 00:14:15,053
[Deib coughing]

289
00:14:15,553 --> 00:14:16,754
Max, you okay?

290
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:19,024
[both groaning]

291
00:14:19,158 --> 00:14:20,426
I'm okay.

292
00:14:24,964 --> 00:14:25,798
What about you?

293
00:14:30,201 --> 00:14:31,135
[keys jingle]

294
00:14:39,677 --> 00:14:42,413
So, will you accept the job
from Boss?

295
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:47,820
No, bro.
I can't go back to that.

296
00:14:47,952 --> 00:14:50,355
You can't escape Boss.

297
00:14:50,722 --> 00:14:51,990
What if we report him?

298
00:14:52,390 --> 00:14:53,826
Go to the cops!

299
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:56,528
Are you crazy?
You'll drag me down with you!

300
00:14:57,363 --> 00:14:59,465
We can't cross him...

301
00:15:00,298 --> 00:15:02,333
because everyone who does
meets their Maker.

302
00:15:02,467 --> 00:15:03,735
[suspenseful music ends]

303
00:15:06,371 --> 00:15:08,908
[Evita] Chief, I hope you find
who did this fast.

304
00:15:09,041 --> 00:15:09,674
Yes, ma'am.

305
00:15:10,609 --> 00:15:12,477
I hope this doesn't
take as long...

306
00:15:12,610 --> 00:15:16,215
as the case of my other son
who was shot months ago!

307
00:15:16,347 --> 00:15:18,750
That case has no witness.

308
00:15:18,884 --> 00:15:21,386
[cop] Here we have four.

309
00:15:21,519 --> 00:15:25,224
We'll find who did this to Deib
sooner or later.

310
00:15:25,524 --> 00:15:27,826
Think the two cases
are connected?

311
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,394
No.

312
00:15:29,528 --> 00:15:33,432
Based on their statements,
this seems personal.

313
00:15:33,565 --> 00:15:34,966
[cop] Do you have enemies?

314
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:37,201
He made lots of enemies
in school.

315
00:15:37,503 --> 00:15:39,904
That was before, not now.

316
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:43,642
Sir, ma'am, did you see the
faces of those who attacked you?

317
00:15:44,710 --> 00:15:47,712
It was dark
and they were wearing masks.

318
00:15:48,246 --> 00:15:51,283
Sorry, chief, they were
too fast. Sorry, Master.

319
00:15:54,019 --> 00:15:55,321
The one who punched me...

320
00:15:55,721 --> 00:15:57,221
-this fell from his jacket.
-[keys jingle]

321
00:15:59,991 --> 00:16:03,495
Do you know anyone from Southbay
with a grudge against you?

322
00:16:07,765 --> 00:16:08,399
Randall Echavez.

323
00:16:08,533 --> 00:16:11,202
That's him, sure balls!

324
00:16:11,602 --> 00:16:15,139
He's jealous of Master since
he's the MVP at the Interhigh

325
00:16:15,274 --> 00:16:18,576
and in Max's heart! Aww!

326
00:16:20,078 --> 00:16:22,681
Okay, we'll look for Echavez--

327
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:24,082
No.

328
00:16:24,216 --> 00:16:26,118
[Max]
Randall would never do that.

329
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:28,419
You're not on good terms,
but I know him.

330
00:16:28,553 --> 00:16:30,389
He would never hurt anyone.

331
00:16:30,522 --> 00:16:33,325
Max, the guy who punched me,
he has the same height

332
00:16:33,458 --> 00:16:34,860
and build as Echavez--

333
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:37,730
But not the same voice, Deib.

334
00:16:37,863 --> 00:16:41,466
What about the other two?
Could one of them be Echavez?

335
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:44,370
No. RJ would never do this.

336
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,971
Believe me, he's not capable
of such a thing.

337
00:16:49,674 --> 00:16:50,408
Okay.

338
00:16:51,876 --> 00:16:52,977
Okay, Max.

339
00:16:53,445 --> 00:16:54,746
[Daniel] That's it?

340
00:16:54,879 --> 00:16:56,981
Just because Max said it,
you'd believe it immediately?

341
00:16:57,115 --> 00:16:58,283
Come on!

342
00:17:03,822 --> 00:17:04,556
[elevator dings]

343
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:11,430
Tell me the truth.

344
00:17:11,730 --> 00:17:12,096
What?

345
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:14,665
Were you one of the guys
who beat up Deib earlier?

346
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:15,933
What are you talking about?

347
00:17:16,402 --> 00:17:18,737
Some guys messed up his car
and beat him up.

348
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:21,640
We found a Southbay keychain
after. Was that you?

349
00:17:22,106 --> 00:17:22,941
Seriously?!

350
00:17:25,144 --> 00:17:26,612
I've been here all night.

351
00:17:26,944 --> 00:17:28,946
With Grandma and Zell.

352
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:29,882
[RJ] You can ask them.

353
00:17:32,550 --> 00:17:34,385
Is that what you think of me?

354
00:17:37,088 --> 00:17:38,190
Sorry, RJ.

355
00:17:38,624 --> 00:17:40,025
I didn't mean it that way.

356
00:17:40,625 --> 00:17:43,060
I'm not the only one
from Southbay who hates Enrile.

357
00:17:43,662 --> 00:17:45,530
Lots of Benison students...

358
00:17:45,663 --> 00:17:49,268
transferred to Southbay because
of your boyfriend's antics.

359
00:17:49,867 --> 00:17:51,970
What he did to you?

360
00:17:52,104 --> 00:17:52,871
That's nothing compared...

361
00:17:53,005 --> 00:17:54,940
to what he did
to his other victims.

362
00:17:56,442 --> 00:17:58,576
Do you know how toxic
your boyfriend is?

363
00:18:00,112 --> 00:18:00,913
Sorry.

364
00:18:02,079 --> 00:18:03,015
I just thought--

365
00:18:03,382 --> 00:18:04,482
What happened to your arm?

366
00:18:06,151 --> 00:18:07,118
Let's get some first aid
upstairs.

367
00:18:07,251 --> 00:18:08,386
I'm fine.

368
00:18:09,221 --> 00:18:11,890
Hey, Max, RJ!

369
00:18:12,523 --> 00:18:13,925
[Boyet] What are you doing here?

370
00:18:14,326 --> 00:18:19,064
Deib got beaten up earlier.
Thought the culprit was here.

371
00:18:19,198 --> 00:18:20,398
Thankfully, he's not.

372
00:18:20,965 --> 00:18:24,135
Really, how's Deib? Is he okay?
Does he need backup?

373
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:27,506
He's okay now.
No need for backup.

374
00:18:27,873 --> 00:18:29,942
By the way,
did you get the money, Uncle?

375
00:18:30,741 --> 00:18:34,980
Um, yes. I got it! I sent it
to our repairmen in Mindoro.

376
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:37,615
Your Aunt Melba
will oversee everything.

377
00:18:37,749 --> 00:18:39,951
The sooner we can fix the house,
the better.

378
00:18:40,085 --> 00:18:41,519
And don't worry, Uncle.

379
00:18:41,653 --> 00:18:44,957
RJ and I
found a way to pay Deib.

380
00:18:45,390 --> 00:18:46,424
Really?

381
00:18:47,392 --> 00:18:48,926
[Boyet] You shouldn't have...

382
00:18:49,228 --> 00:18:50,362
but thanks, RJ.

383
00:18:50,496 --> 00:18:53,132
My niece is lucky
to have you as her best friend.

384
00:18:53,664 --> 00:18:54,932
No problem, Uncle.

385
00:18:57,301 --> 00:18:58,403
This calls for a group hug!

386
00:19:00,038 --> 00:19:00,739
[Boyet] Group hug!

387
00:19:01,205 --> 00:19:02,173
Group hug!

388
00:19:11,549 --> 00:19:14,419
[indistinct nervous chatter]

389
00:19:14,553 --> 00:19:15,820
DEIB MADE OUR LIVES HELL!

390
00:19:23,761 --> 00:19:26,097
[Naih]
Stop me! I'm scared, Mine!

391
00:19:31,936 --> 00:19:35,039
-[Naih] Oh my God!
-[Lorde] Oh boy!

392
00:19:35,173 --> 00:19:35,907
The other students are worried

393
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:38,175
that there will be
more retaliation,

394
00:19:38,309 --> 00:19:39,778
not just against you, Deib,

395
00:19:40,144 --> 00:19:41,246
but on them as well.

396
00:19:41,712 --> 00:19:42,881
I will be calling
a student assembly later

397
00:19:43,015 --> 00:19:44,982
to tell everyone
what I will be telling you now.

398
00:19:49,387 --> 00:19:50,255
What's this?

399
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:53,392
I spoke with the principal
of Southbay.

400
00:19:54,092 --> 00:19:56,595
He's not tolerating their
students' misconduct either.

401
00:19:57,461 --> 00:19:58,997
He got a confession...

402
00:19:59,131 --> 00:20:00,999
from the students involved
in the vandalization of your car

403
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:02,267
and our school.

404
00:20:03,035 --> 00:20:03,801
As punishment,

405
00:20:04,169 --> 00:20:06,238
they will clean up the wall
they defaced.

406
00:20:06,672 --> 00:20:07,905
Those are their names.

407
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:10,409
Echavez is not here...

408
00:20:11,175 --> 00:20:11,910
[Headmaster] They all to claim
to be victims

409
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:14,779
of your infamous
"Project: Blocked."

410
00:20:15,646 --> 00:20:16,748
For them, it's not enough
that you will just

411
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:19,183
do 40 hours of school service.

412
00:20:19,550 --> 00:20:20,786
They want you expelled.

413
00:20:24,122 --> 00:20:26,057
Sorry for dragging the school
into all this.

414
00:20:26,458 --> 00:20:28,160
Don't say sorry to me.

415
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:31,028
Apologize to those you bullied.

416
00:20:31,663 --> 00:20:33,265
But what if that's enough, sir?

417
00:20:34,398 --> 00:20:36,167
What if they don't forgive me?

418
00:20:36,602 --> 00:20:39,070
Because
if I'm being really honest,

419
00:20:40,439 --> 00:20:43,075
I still can't forgive myself
for what I did.

420
00:20:43,808 --> 00:20:45,143
Everything I did.

421
00:20:45,777 --> 00:20:47,112
I know how you feel.

422
00:20:47,878 --> 00:20:50,414
And I will tell you
what your grandpa told me...

423
00:20:50,848 --> 00:20:52,817
when I was still studying here
in Benison.

424
00:20:53,518 --> 00:20:54,452
He said...

425
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:59,223
that the past cannot be changed,
forgotten, or edited.

426
00:20:59,924 --> 00:21:03,761
It just needs to be accepted,
as it is.

427
00:21:04,663 --> 00:21:05,931
He told me that...

428
00:21:06,064 --> 00:21:09,534
If you cannot accept your past,
you punish yourself

429
00:21:09,667 --> 00:21:11,603
in ways that hurt more than...

430
00:21:11,737 --> 00:21:13,739
any other punishment
the world can give you.

431
00:21:14,673 --> 00:21:16,674
Wallowing in shame

432
00:21:16,974 --> 00:21:18,644
will take away your power

433
00:21:18,777 --> 00:21:21,212
from the things
you can actually change.

434
00:21:22,213 --> 00:21:25,284
You kids today like saying
people should be cancelled,

435
00:21:26,117 --> 00:21:28,819
as if you can really
cancel human beings.

436
00:21:30,388 --> 00:21:32,190
More than cancelling people,

437
00:21:32,723 --> 00:21:34,925
we should call them out
for their mistakes

438
00:21:35,826 --> 00:21:39,096
while recognizing
their capacity for change.

439
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:44,303
That was Max's point
at my trial.

440
00:21:44,435 --> 00:21:45,202
Exactly.

441
00:21:45,903 --> 00:21:47,471
Prove to yourself and to them

442
00:21:47,605 --> 00:21:50,474
that everything Ms. Del Valle
said at your trial was true.

443
00:21:51,876 --> 00:21:54,346
Show them you've changed.

444
00:22:04,588 --> 00:22:06,325
[Daniel] Were you so bored
with your charmed life,

445
00:22:06,458 --> 00:22:09,326
you just had to create problems
for yourself?

446
00:22:10,761 --> 00:22:14,965
Maybe your mom and I
didn't raise you well

447
00:22:15,634 --> 00:22:18,603
if you're being applauded
for meeting the bare minimum

448
00:22:18,737 --> 00:22:20,337
of being a decent human being.

449
00:22:20,471 --> 00:22:21,272
Well Evita...

450
00:22:22,874 --> 00:22:25,176
we failed as parents.

451
00:22:26,411 --> 00:22:27,112
[Evita] Hon,

452
00:22:27,679 --> 00:22:29,548
let's not rehash that.

453
00:22:30,449 --> 00:22:35,086
Your son has apologized
and has changed, right?

454
00:22:38,123 --> 00:22:41,292
And Deib will make it up
to those he hurt, sir.

455
00:22:43,662 --> 00:22:44,762
[Daniel] But, I have to say.

456
00:22:45,730 --> 00:22:50,201
My son, for all his faults, is
lucky to have someone like you,

457
00:22:50,335 --> 00:22:52,537
who believes in him
the way you do.

458
00:22:52,871 --> 00:22:54,239
But here's my question -

459
00:22:55,339 --> 00:22:58,375
are you like that with everyone?
Or just my son?

460
00:23:00,912 --> 00:23:02,547
When you love someone,

461
00:23:02,980 --> 00:23:04,516
you never give up on them.

462
00:23:06,484 --> 00:23:09,587
You will look for
what's worth loving in them.

463
00:23:10,355 --> 00:23:13,825
And I always find what's
worth loving about your son.

464
00:23:19,530 --> 00:23:20,898
Well, hon?

465
00:23:30,674 --> 00:23:31,410
You know what...

466
00:23:33,077 --> 00:23:34,445
Headmaster at least...

467
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:37,982
he believes in me.

468
00:23:40,419 --> 00:23:41,952
But my dad...

469
00:23:43,121 --> 00:23:44,756
thinks I'm a lost cause.

470
00:23:45,289 --> 00:23:48,425
Maybe he's just stressed, Deib.

471
00:23:48,559 --> 00:23:52,364
Nah. I don't think so, Max.

472
00:23:54,499 --> 00:23:58,303
I sometimes wonder if my dad
ever really wanted me.

473
00:23:59,203 --> 00:23:59,770
Deib...

474
00:23:59,904 --> 00:24:02,039
All I do is disappoint him.

475
00:24:03,107 --> 00:24:05,376
I can't make him happy.

476
00:24:06,411 --> 00:24:08,078
I'm honestly
thinking about it...

477
00:24:09,213 --> 00:24:14,286
even if I cure my brother
or solve his case,

478
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:19,057
it won't amount to anything
in my dad's eyes.

479
00:24:25,063 --> 00:24:27,898
Deib, I'm sure,
you and your dad will be okay,

480
00:24:29,366 --> 00:24:35,707
but I want you to know,
I'm so proud of you.

481
00:24:36,208 --> 00:24:37,741
And I'm happy with you.

482
00:24:38,108 --> 00:24:40,545
I have faith
that the people you hurt

483
00:24:41,645 --> 00:24:46,518
will see your sincerity
and forgive you in time.

484
00:24:50,755 --> 00:24:51,623
I hope so.

485
00:25:00,164 --> 00:25:01,266
I'm so sorry, Mr. Quisimbing.

486
00:25:01,398 --> 00:25:02,834
I promise you
it won't happen again.

487
00:25:02,968 --> 00:25:05,170
What's important is they
learned their lesson.

488
00:25:10,741 --> 00:25:11,576
Mr. Enrile,

489
00:25:12,210 --> 00:25:13,345
what are you doing here?

490
00:25:14,346 --> 00:25:15,180
Sir!

491
00:25:15,881 --> 00:25:17,281
Sir, I got this.

492
00:25:18,016 --> 00:25:19,984
It's my fault anyway.

493
00:25:21,886 --> 00:25:23,255
Guys, sorry.

494
00:25:24,823 --> 00:25:26,423
Sorry for all the trauma,
humiliation,

495
00:25:27,491 --> 00:25:29,827
and hurt that I've caused you.
Sorry.

496
00:25:30,494 --> 00:25:33,832
Sorry, too,
for what we did to your car.

497
00:25:33,964 --> 00:25:35,599
I was the one who beat you up.

498
00:25:36,134 --> 00:25:37,602
[Jaybee]
You shouldn't do this alone.

499
00:25:41,239 --> 00:25:45,109
[poignant music playing]

500
00:26:00,090 --> 00:26:01,326
[Headmaster] Rivalry no more!

501
00:26:01,459 --> 00:26:03,929
Benison and Southbay boys
all grown up!

502
00:26:04,496 --> 00:26:05,262
[Kristine Gelito]
Proud of you, Deib!

503
00:26:05,396 --> 00:26:06,330
[JP Raymundo] Good job, boys!

504
00:26:06,463 --> 00:26:07,265
[Daisy Albano]
A sight for sore eyes!

505
00:26:07,398 --> 00:26:08,599
[Carmel Daza]
Hope this continues!

506
00:26:08,732 --> 00:26:10,201
Guys, snacks...

507
00:26:11,702 --> 00:26:13,337
Bro, thank you!

508
00:26:16,974 --> 00:26:18,242
Bro, thank you!

509
00:26:20,111 --> 00:26:21,278
Here, guys,

510
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:22,547
cookies.

511
00:26:22,681 --> 00:26:23,347
They're delicious!

512
00:26:24,048 --> 00:26:25,450
It's actually my favorite.

513
00:26:26,785 --> 00:26:28,118
Sure, thank you.

514
00:26:33,357 --> 00:26:34,224
Yummy!

515
00:26:35,894 --> 00:26:37,394
Thanks for earlier, guys.

516
00:26:49,074 --> 00:26:50,575
What did I do to you again?

517
00:26:51,576 --> 00:26:53,010
You tried to fit me
into my locker.

518
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:57,615
Jaybee Jose, right?

519
00:26:57,749 --> 00:26:58,549
You remember me?

520
00:26:59,084 --> 00:26:59,884
Yeah,

521
